WEBVTT

00:00.187 --> 00:02.021
<i>Previously on</i>
<i>The Borgias...</i>

00:02.089 --> 00:03.990
Giovanni Sforza.

00:04.058 --> 00:06.793
And my cousin,
Catherina Sforza.

00:06.861 --> 00:08.825
You would have a taste
of vengeance.

00:08.893 --> 00:10.697
Giovanni Sforza-
he proved ungallant?

00:10.765 --> 00:12.450
He betrayed our father,
the pope.

00:12.551 --> 00:13.796
If he misused you,

00:13.863 --> 00:15.332
he shall pay a
different kind of price.

00:15.400 --> 00:17.934
You think the blood of the
Borgia pope could cure us?

00:18.001 --> 00:20.034
We could bathe in it
together, Majesty.

00:20.102 --> 00:21.908
<i>Catherina Sforza</i>
<i>rides with the French.</i>

00:21.976 --> 00:23.212
She has the arms she needed

00:23.280 --> 00:25.214
and has retired to
her castle at Forli.

00:25.315 --> 00:26.515
And we forgive her?

00:26.584 --> 00:28.455
Priorities can change,
Cardinal Borgia.

00:28.522 --> 00:31.728
<i>The French have laid</i>
<i>waste to the papal states.</i>

00:31.795 --> 00:35.031
Our proposal is that
the armies combine-

00:35.099 --> 00:37.132
<i>to rid us of this</i>
<i>French plague.</i>

00:37.200 --> 00:39.335
You think we can
defeat the French?

00:39.403 --> 00:40.801
We can strike them at night.

00:40.869 --> 00:42.937
<i>They move like smoke</i>
<i>in the darkness.</i>

00:45.940 --> 00:47.841
<i>Do you have anything to</i>
<i>confess about this past night?</i>

00:47.908 --> 00:51.311
My night was as satisfactory
as I'm sure was yours.

00:52.413 --> 00:54.580
<i>I would beg your</i>
<i>permission to investigate</i>

00:54.648 --> 00:56.785
the office of public
works even further.

00:56.853 --> 00:58.521
Found more irregularities?

00:58.588 --> 01:01.057
There are so many in
this Vatican of yours.

01:01.125 --> 01:03.360
<i>You are?</i>
<i>Nicolo Machiavelli.</i>

01:03.427 --> 01:05.295
Ambassador to
the House of Medici.

01:05.363 --> 01:07.532
The Medici family are
bankers to the world.

01:07.633 --> 01:08.966
To the Vatican itself.

01:09.034 --> 01:11.736
<i>Father Savonarola</i>
<i>calls it usury.</i>

01:11.803 --> 01:15.640
This pope is a
lecherous abomination!

01:15.708 --> 01:18.411
Florence, you will
pay for your greed-

01:18.479 --> 01:21.983
when he drags
you to perdition!

01:22.051 --> 01:24.519
Savonarola prophesied
the end of days-

01:24.621 --> 01:26.256
not the murder of the pope.

01:26.324 --> 01:29.359
If I had his approval,
would I have yours?

